Privacy Policy — Mise en Place
Effective Date: May 31, 2026
Version: 2.0

1. Introduction
Mise en Place ("the Service") is a private, household meal-planning application
operated for personal use by two named individuals. It is not a commercial
product, is not offered to the public, and is not operated by a registered
business entity.

2. What We Collect
The Service does NOT collect phone numbers and does NOT send or receive SMS
messages. (Earlier versions used Twilio SMS; that has been removed.)

The Service stores only recipe-related data in a private Supabase (PostgreSQL)
database:
  - Recipes (name, ingredients, instructions, source URL) submitted by the
    authorized users, typically via Instagram links.
  - Weekly meal plans and the generated shopping list.
  - Submission and pipeline-run metadata (timestamps, status) for debugging.

No behavioral tracking, analytics, advertising identifiers, or personal contact
information is collected.

3. How Recipes Are Submitted
Recipes are added by sending a link (usually Instagram) or a recipe name to the
Service's ingest endpoint — from the web app or a personal iOS Share-sheet
Shortcut. The linked page/caption is fetched and parsed into a structured
recipe. We do not log in to, or access, any user's Instagram account; only the
content of links you explicitly submit is fetched.

4. Third Parties
Submitted content is processed by the Anthropic Claude API (recipe parsing and
shopping-list consolidation) and stored in Supabase. The shopping list is
written to Todoist. We do not sell, rent, or otherwise share data with any
other third party.

5. Data Storage and Security
Data is stored in a private Supabase database with row-level security enabled
and is not publicly accessible. Secrets (API keys, the ingest token, and
Todoist credentials) are stored as encrypted environment variables in GitHub
Secrets and the hosting platform, accessible only to the account owner.

6. Data Retention
Recipe and plan data is retained for as long as the Service is in operation.
Pipeline-run logs are retained for 90 days. Upon request, the account owner can
delete any stored data.

7. Contact
This Service is privately operated. For any privacy-related questions, please
contact the account owner directly.

8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy from time to time; the effective date above reflects
the most recent revision.

